lead_paragraph: Contradictory reports of Marshal Italo Balbo's death in Cyrenaica are bound to cause speculation. According to the first announcement from Rome, his plane, with nine others aboard, several of whom were noncombatants, crashed in flames after a battle with British aircraft over Tobruk.
